Day 14: Transactions & ACID Properties

Topic:
Database Transactions and ACID Properties

Learning Objectives:

• Understand database transactions and their importance
• Learn the four ACID properties: Atomicity, Consistency, Isolation, and Durability
• Understand how transactions maintain data reliability and integrity
• Learn how to use BEGIN, COMMIT, and ROLLBACK statements in SQL
• Explore real-world examples such as banking transactions

Activities / Deliverables:

• Simulate a bank transfer transaction in MySQL
• Use BEGIN to start a transaction
• Perform debit and credit operations between accounts
• Intentionally trigger a failure during the transaction
• Use ROLLBACK to undo incomplete changes
• Verify data consistency after rollback and successful commit
• Document transaction flow and observations

Tools / Tech:

• MySQL 8
• MySQL Workbench

